    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#ferri1923"/>, n. <citedRange>9</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.342</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>032600</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64233"><name nymRef="#Θεύχρηστος">Θευχρή<supplied reason="lost">στω</supplied></name></persName>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1"><lem resp="#ferri1923">Θευχρή<supplied reason="lost">στω</supplied></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SEG"><expan><abbr>Θευχρή</abbr><ex>στω</ex></expan></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Autel</supplied> appartenant à Theukhrèstos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altar</supplied> belonging to Theuchrestos.</p>            
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altare</supplied> appartenente a Theuchrestos.</p>            
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Such personal names, indicating the owner of the altar, are often abbreviated (see commentary at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr032000</ref>). However,
                    as we could not check the inscription, we follow Ferri in restoring the end of the name, <foreign xml:lang="la">contra</foreign> SEG.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
